original: Högberg, Folke, vägingenjör, Marie-stad, f. 5/5/01 i Motala av miss. Lars Erik H. o. Sigrid Braune. G. 40 m. Astrid Lundgren. Barn: Hans-Erik f. 41, Thomas 47. — Stud:ex. v. norra real i Sthlm 20, civ:ing. v. KTH 24. Res. t. USA 27-30 f. stud. av hus-byggn. o. konstr. Anst. h. stat. provn:-anst. 26-27, kontr. f. brobyggn., avd:-ing. h. väg- o. vattenbyggn :styr. i Jämtl., Norrb. o. Västern. 1. 30-43, väging. f. projekter. i Skarab. 1. fr. 44. Led. av Sv. tekn:fören., Sv. betong-fören., Sv. vägfören., SVR.
translated: Högberg, Folke, road engineer from Marie-stad, born on May 5th, 1901 in Motala to missionary Lars Erik H. and Sigrid Braune. Married to Astrid Lundgren in 1940 and has two children: Hans-Erik (born in 1941) and Thomas (born in 1947). He completed his student exam at Norra Real in Stockholm in 1920 and received a civil engineer degree from KTH in 1924. He then traveled to the United States from 1927 to 1930 to study house-building and construction. He worked at the state testing facility in 1926-1927, as a contract worker for the construction of bridges, and in the road and water building control of Jämtl., Norrb. and Västern. He was a road engineer for Skarab from 1944 onwards. He is a member of the Swedish Engineering Society, the Swedish Concrete Society, the Swedish Road Association, and the Royal Swedish Academy of Engineering Sciences.

memberOf.name: Royal Swedish Academy of Engineering Sciences
